**What is API Hooking?**

API hooking involves injecting a piece of code into a process's memory space, allowing the hooking code to intercept and modify the behavior of system calls. This can be achieved by hooking into the API (Application Programming Interface) of the operating system, which provides a set of functions that applications can use to interact with the system.

